  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6553.57 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-16.3B) and positive gamma at 6580 (+5.1B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they're short gamma in breakout regime. The concentrated negative GEX walls from 6525-6550 create a dangerous amplification zone where any dip will trigger aggressive dealer buying, while a push above 6580 forces them to sell into strength. The wall_break and gex_surge events signal we're in a critical inflection point where small moves get magnified - watch for violent moves away from the 6550 anchor.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect explosive moves in either direction as dealers amplify any breakout from this tight range.",
